# Cost Optimization

Always minimize operational cost. Never implement expensive operations when cheaper alternatives exist.

## Minimize

- **OpenAI tokens** — trim prompts, cache embeddings, limit context windows
- **Redis memory** — TTLs, right-sized keys, avoid storing large blobs
- **MongoDB reads/writes** — indexes, projection, pagination, avoid redundant queries
- **S3 requests** — batch operations, lifecycle policies, CDN caching
- **Cloudflare requests** — cache static assets, reduce origin round-trips
- **Network traffic** — compress payloads, avoid chatty APIs
- **CPU & RAM** — right-size containers, async where possible, stream don't buffer

## Design Questions

- Can this be cached?
- Can this run asynchronously?
- Can we batch this operation?
- Is this the smallest model that meets quality requirements?
